Almost all data has been purged on the terminal, but there is one message oddly left behind for someone to see, or perhaps something that escaped the data purge.

<cÿ~ >Things will be difficult moving forward, but my work here has shown resounding success. Taking Drear's research and utilizing it as a weapon in itself feels like a stroke of genius, but I can't forget the years of pain and effort taken to reach this. Years of gaining trust on Odacer-Faustin. Years of searching the tower. Years of working my way up the chain in Czerka. But now I've succeeded in my pursuits.

Let this facility be proof of my successes here, now. No one survives, though. Can't have any loose ends. That's why I've taken the liberty of administering this "sickness" into the food supply. It's possible one or two of them could be immune, but--[DATA CORRUPTED]-- getting back on track, I'll move forth to further this goal and proceed where Drear failed.</c>

One more thing that can be gleamed from the information remaining on the termal is a word: "Vecten"
The hologram here seems to show an icy world of some sort, though there is no readout showing exactly which one.
Standard issue beer mug. Sad looking when its empty, but still good in a pinch. And the design on the rim can make a good impression in a brawl.
A good sauce pan is every cook's friend.  Both for boiling potatoes, and restoring order. Grab this pan, open one can of whoop-ass, and do lunch!

The controls are inaccessible, showing a single message on the screen.

<cÿ  >STATION HANGAR BAY ACCESS | LOCKDOWN WHILE TRACTOR BEAM ACTIVE</c>

Value.value: Exitting the turbolift, you enter a rather well-lit office. Holobooks, artifacts, and other things can be seen across the walls. In the center of the room is a large desk. The smell, while still being that of a musty space station, is far more pleasant here as it lacks the smell of rot and decay that you had to deal with until now.
